|death_cause = [[Crucifixion of Jesus|Crucifixion]]<ref>James Dunn states that the baptism and crucifixion of Jesus "command almost universal assent" and "rank so high on the 'almost impossible to doubt or deny' scale of historical facts" that they are often the starting points for the study of the historical Jesus ({{harvnb|Dunn|2003|p=339}}). 
* Bart Ehrman states that the crucifixion of Jesus on the orders of Pontius Pilate is the most certain element about him ({{harvnb| Ehrman|1999|p=101}}).
* John Dominic Crossan states that the crucifixion of Jesus is as certain as any historical fact can be ({{harvnb|Crossan|Watts|1999|p=96}}). 
* Eddy and Boyd state that it is now "firmly established" that there is non-Christian confirmation of the crucifixion of Jesus ({{harvnb|Eddy|Boyd|2007|p=173}}).</ref>
